<h2 id="most-people-measure-the-wrong-thing">Most people measure the wrong thing</h2>

<p>When we talk about AI productivity, we measure outputs. Did the task complete? How fast? How many tokens did it cost?</p>

<p>These are real metrics. But they miss the layer underneath.</p>

<p>Think about what actually happens in a coding session with an AI. You describe a task. The model responds with something close to what you meant ŌĆö but not quite. You correct it. It adjusts. You verify the result, notice a filename doesnŌĆÖt match, fix the reference, check the directory, confirm the output.</p>

