<p>IŌĆÖve started calling the second kind <em>alignment tax</em>: the extra cycles spent not on the work itself, but on establishing the shared reality the work requires.</p>

<p>Alignment tax is not a bug. ItŌĆÖs not even avoidable. ItŌĆÖs a structural feature of how language models and humans collaborate. The model has no persistent memory of your project. It doesnŌĆÖt know your file naming conventions, your aesthetic preferences, or that you named the file <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">context_window.svg</code> with an underscore. You know all of that. The model knows none of it until you tell it ŌĆö and you often donŌĆÖt know you need to tell it until it guesses wrong.</p>

