<p>But hereŌĆÖs what IŌĆÖve noticed: most developers I talk to underestimate how much of their ŌĆ£promptingŌĆØ is actually alignment work. They describe sessions as productive when they completed tasks. They donŌĆÖt track the ratio of task work to alignment work. They donŌĆÖt ask whether a specific category of task reliably generates more alignment overhead than others.</p>

